                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d594">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/452: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Ethiopia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">George</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Addis Ababa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-07-03T17:00:00+02:35"
                            >July 3, 1935—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 3—11:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>51. My telegram No. 50.<note n="33" xml:id="d594fn33">July 3, noon, <ref
                            target="#pg_612">p. 612</ref>.</note> I have learned confidentially
                    Emperor will address a note to me tomorrow invoking Kellogg Pact<note n="34"
                        xml:id="d594fn34">
                        <ref target="frus1928v01#pg_153">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1928, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 153</ref>.</note> and will release
                    copies to other Legations and press.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">George</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
